{
  "text": "(ii)Transcriptional Induction of UPR -ATF6 Pathway. ATF6 is an ER-resident type II transmembrane protein with an N-terminal cytoplasmic region containing bZIP and DNA transactivation domains, and a C-terminal lumenal region that senses ER stress [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
